from Harvard, and the

09:52.479 --> 09:58.205
Secretaries of Defense from MIT and Stanford. And 
that

09:58.225 --> 10:02.750
helps the image of greatness. And what this all 
boiled down to was that we wanted to try to insert

10:02.770 --> 10:09.677
Texas A&M more into national and international 
affairs, more into attacking the great

10:10.028 --> 10:23.709
problems of our time, if you want to be that 
grandiose about it. And it was just felt that in

10:23.729 --> 10:37.690
addition to having a damn good academic program, 
undergraduate and graduate, in addition to

10:23.729 --> 10:37.690
having a damn good research program,

10:23.729 --> 10:37.690
we wanted to do more. we wanted to insert ourselves 
into some of the national decision-making

10:38.243 --> 10:47.071
processes. And I remember writing Mr. Benson a 
memo back in, I think, 75, where I told him I was

10:47.092 --> 11:06.310
concerned about Texas A&M's image as, I think my 
words were, a football, military-oriented Cal

10:47.092 --> 11:06.310
College. an image that

11:07.994 --> 11:26.800
to some extent was

11:07.994 --> 11:26.800
deserved, but to a large extent was not deserved. 
And that I thought we needed to have a, I just called

11:26.820 --> 11:32.848
it a special research program, that would be aimed 
at dispelling that image and creating a new image.

11:32.868 --> 11:36.313
And so I told him some notions I had about how to 
proceed with this. He, I told him that as I surveyed

11:37.880 --> 11:55.947
the faculty that was appropriate to this effort, 
and this has to be guys, I mean these have to be

11:37.880 --> 11:55.947
faculty members who have

11:37.880 --> 11:55.947
national or international reputation. People 
that were sort of like E.F. Hutton, you know, when

11:55.967 --> 12:03.718
they taught folks, listen,

11:55.967 --> 12:03.718
we didn't have them. within

12:04.981 --> 12:16.394
the College of Engineering. I could count them,

12:16.414 --> 12:26.666
